Kill all tcpdump process once the dump files is larger then 20M

How to use:
2.	Put monitor_file_size.sh to any dirctory, for example:/cluster/tcpdump/
3.	chmod +x /cluster/tcpdump/monitor_file_size.sh
4.	run tcpdump
5.	/cluster/tcpdump/monitor_file_size.sh <file name>
for example: /cluster/tcpdump/monitor_file_size.sh /cluster/tcpdump/cap1.cap 
